The paper deals with structural parameterization of the Vertex Cover problem, which is a classic problem in computational complexity theory. The paper introduces the concept of a pseudoforest modulator and shows that Vertex Cover admits a polynomial kernel when parameterized by the size of the pseudoforest modulator. This suggests that the paper could belong to the Discrete Mathematics (cs.DM), Data Structures and Algorithms (cs.DS), Computational Complexity (cs.CC), Computational Geometry (cs.CG), or Graph Theory (cs.GT) sub-categories.
